<doc f='linux-5.3.1/include/scsi/sg.h' l='192'>/* Largest size (in bytes) a single scatter-gather list element can have.
   The value used by the driver is &apos;max(SG_SCATTER_SZ, PAGE_SIZE)&apos;.
   This value should be a power of 2 (and may be rounded up internally).
   If scatter-gather is not supported by adapter then this value is the
   largest data block that can be read/written by a single scsi command. */</doc>
